rComments: Truly loves teaching/helping her students. Her enthusiasm and empathy make her the best instructor I've had in my years at the University of Illinois.

She is absolutely amazing! A wonderful TA who will help you and make you into a better public speaker. She is eccentric and has a unique personality but she is very smart and it shows in her lectures.
She seemed to really like teaching, and kept class interesting.  Course material and schedule was a little tough, but i think that was the curriculum, not her idea.

she's nice, and flexible if you have problems. she was strict about attending class on unofficial which was extremely annoying. she grades fairly, and bases a lot on participation which is easy enough.
